## Executive Briefing
[cite_start]As agents operate at speeds exceeding human peer-review capacity, the resulting cognitive load triggers a breakdown in oversight, leading to "blind approval" and a loss of data sovereignty[cite: 112, 113]. [cite_start]This archive establishes the $A_m$ model as an active governance layer to bridge this gap[cite: 114, 116].

## The Refactored Mathematical Model
[cite_start]To align with behavioral reality, adherence is modeled as an inverse relationship to complexity[cite: 138]:

$$A_m = \frac{V_s}{O_c \cdot F_a}$$

* [cite_start]**$V_s$ (Verification Simplicity):** The ease of validating machine-generated output[cite: 106].
* **$O_c$ (Output Complexity):** The technical density and entropy of the task.
* **$F_a$ (Agentic Friction):** Cumulative cognitive load and "Mental Noise"[cite: 134, 138].

